  "source": "Axiom:\n. \"Axiom of Choice\"\ngiven:\n. X is \\set\nwhere:\n. forAll: A is \\set\n  where:\n  . A \"in\" X\n  then:\n  . not:\n    . A = \\empty.set\nthen:\n. exists: f is \\choice.function:on{X}\nDocumented:\n. description: \"Let $X$ be a collection of non-empty sets. Then there exists a choice function on $X$. For finite collections this is a theorem, but in the infinite case there is in general no rule specifying which element to choose, and so the existence of a choice function must be taken as an axiom. Adjoining it to the axioms of ZF yields the system ZFC.\"\nId: \"fe49a375-61dd-4bb2-895f-4afdf7c10baf\"",
